Bay of Fundy Scallop Assessment Script Workflow

Brittany Wilson

2021-05-18

Overview

This document is intended as a guide to the inshore scallop assessment workflow and the R-scripts that are used in the assessment process. This document can be used as a Rmarkdown allowing the user to open the required scripts within Rstudio, or be read as a html or PDF document where the user can review the workflow and manually locate the scripts within the specified directory.

The Bay of Fundy assessment is separated by Scallop Production areas:

SPA1A, SPA1B, SPA3, SPA4 and SPA5, and SPA6

Bay of Fundy

1. Standard Depth

  • Script Directory:

    To be your forked Marscal Inshore repository path (e.g. C:/Users/WILSONB/Documents/GitHub/Inshore)

  • Purpose:

    This script is used to pull bathymetry values from survey point locations and appends it to survey data (i.e. standardize depth values).

  • Output(s):

    towsdd_StdDepth.csv, BoFMeanDepths.csv (derived from this depth data, does not change and will not need to be reproduced. Used in 7. Growth Rates (Growth)

  • Output Directory(s):

    ESS:/Inshore/StandardDepth

COMMIT CHANGES

Ensure that all changes made to the script Standardize_depth.R have been saved and pushed to Marscal Inshore repository before continuing!

2. Meat Weight - Shell Height and Condition modeling (Growth)

  • Script Directory:

    Y:/Inshore/BoF/2022/Assessment/Scripts/Growth (eventually to be our forked Marscal/inshore repository, e.g. C:/Users/WILSONB/Documents/GitHub/Inshore/BoF/Growth)

  • Purpose:

    The MeatWeightShellHeight.R scripts models meat weight with shell height, depth and tow.

  • Overview: Edits to model object YYYY will need to be made every assessment (e.g. MWTSHBF.YYYY)

  1. Set up data for modelling:

    • Query detailed meat weight/shell height sampling data from database (scallsur.scwgthgt) for specified cruises (SPA1A1B4and5, SPA3, SPA6).
    • Query shell height bin data from database (scallsur.scliveres) for specified cruises (SPA1A1B4and5, SPA3, SPA6).
    • Format and merge depth information (from towsdd_StdDepth.csv) to the meat weight/shell height dataframe (BFdetail).
    • Format and merge depth information (from towsdd_StdDepth.csv) to the shell height bin data (BFlivefreq).

  2. Run the Meat Weight Shell Height Model:

    • Subset for the survey year, shell height > 40mm

    • Centre Height and Depth values (e.g log height - mean(log height))

    • Run model (GLM) predicting meat weight as a function of fixed effects shell height and depth and random effect shell height grouped by tow.

      \(EQUATION HERE\)

    • Assess/plot residuals (full area and by tow) and fitted data.

  3. Predicting:

    • Subset for the survey year
    • Centre Height values (log of the midpoint of the bins - mean of the log height)
    • Centre Depth values (log depth - mean(test.data$Log.DEPTH)
    • Create a matrix of depths by tow to use in predict function
    • Predict using Random effects for tows where meat weight shell height samples were taken - gives MWT-SH relationship for one individual
    • Predict using Fixed effects for tows where meat weight shell height samples were not taken - gives MWT-SH relationship for one individual
    • Multiply prediction matrix (weight) by live numbers to get weight/bin size

  4. Condition data for Spatial plots

    • centre depth using same mean depth used in the MWTSH model (mean(test.data$Log.DEPTH))

    • Subset for tows that were sampled for meat weight shell height

    • Predict a meat weight for shell height 100mm for sampled tows only.

      \(EQUATION HERE\)

  • Output(s):

    • SPA 1A, 1B, 4 and 5

      • BFliveweight.csv (MWTSH)

      • BFConditionforMap.csv (Condition)

      • BFgrowthYYYY.RData

      • Figures: BFtowdepthYYYY.png, MWTSHBFYYYY.png, MWTSHBFYYYY_towresid.png, and MWTSHBFYYYY_towfit.png

      • Model summary - MWTSHBFYYYY_ModelSummary.txt

    • SPA 3

      • BIliveweight.csv (MWTSH)

      • BIConditionforMap.csv (Condition)

      • BIgrowthYYYY.RData

      • Figures: BItowdepthYYYY.png, MWTSHBIYYYY.png, MWTSHBIYYYY_towresid.png, and MWTSHBIYYYY_towfit.png

      • Model summary - MWTSHBIYYYY_ModelSummary.txt

    • SPA 6

      • GMliveweight.csv (MWTSH)

      • GMConditionforMap.csv (Condition)

      • GMgrowthYYYY.RData

      • Figures: GMtowdepthYYYY.png, MWTSHGMYYYY.png, MWTSHGMYYYY_towresid.png, and MWTSHGMYYYY_towfit.png

      • Model summary - MWTSHGMYYYY_ModelSummary.txt

    • Other

      • AREA_ConditionTimeSeries.png (Condition Time series)


  • Output Directory(s):

4. VonB (Growth)

  • Purpose: These scripts model growth using the von-Bertalanffy growth equation for specified cruises (SPA1A1B4and5, SPA3, SPA6).

    NOTE: This script does not need to be run every year. New aging data is required for updated outputs.

  • Overview:

Set up data for modelling: - Query detailed meat weight/shell height sampling data from database (scallsur.scwgthgt) for specified cruises (SPA1A1B4and5, SPA3, SPA6). - Format data for the model - Run the VonB

\(L_t = L_\infty(1-e^{-K(t)})\)

Where:

\(L_t\) = Length at age \(t\)

\(L_\infty\) = asymptotic length (length at which growth rate is zero) - estimated from the data

\(K\) = Brody growth coeff (rate of growth towards asymptote) - estimated from the data

\(t\) = scallop age (years)

  • Script Directory: To be your forked Marscal Inshore repository path (e.g. C:/Users/WILSONB/Documents/GitHub/Inshore/BoF/Growth)

  • Output(s):

  • Output Directory(s):

COMMIT CHANGES

Ensure that all changes made to VonB.R scripts have been saved and pushed to Marscal Inshore repository before continuing!

5. Shell Height Frequencies (Growth)

  • Purpose: This script produces plots of shell height frequencies for specified strata by year, and calculates commercial mean shell height in year t (\(\bar{L}\)) and uses parameters from the VonB growth model to predict how much a shell of height \(L\) will grow in one year.

    NOTE - requires the script BoFstratadef.R (Inshore github repo) and PEDstrata package to run. NOTE - TO DO: source the .RData files created by the vonB scripts (i.e. read in the outputs directly instead of hardcoding them in)

  • Overview:

  • For each area (SPA1A, SPA1B, SPA3, SPA4 and SPA6) scripts are run separately.

    • Query shell height bin data from database (scallsur.scliveres) for specified Strata.

    • Calculate shell height frequency for each year by strata. NOTE - Look into using sf to stratify

    • Calculate stratified shell height frequency for all of area (SPA1A, SPA1B, SPA3, SPA4 and SPA6) by year

    • Plot shell height frequencies for each year (last 7 years)

    • Calculate \(\bar{L}\) for all of area (SPA1A, SPA1B, SPA3, SPA4 and SPA6) by year for commercial and recruit sizes

    • Predict \(\bar{L}\) in \(t+1\):

    \(\bar{L}_{t+1} = L_\infty * (1-e^{-e^{logK}}) + (e^{-e^{logK}}) * (\bar{L})\)

    • Calculate \(\bar{L}\) for each subarea for plotting

    • Repeat Tow plots (SPA1B - query from scallsur.sccomparisontows)

See Y:/Inshore/BoF/SurveyDesignTables/Areas for BoF Assessment modelling_Notes.docx for more details on substrata areas.

  1. SPA1A:

    • 2 to 8 mile = Strata 6 and 7

    • 8 to 16 mile = Strata 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20

    • Mid-Bay South = Strata 39

  2. SPA1B:

    • Mid-Bay North = Strata 38 (Gets separated into East and West strata) NOTE Check east and west in script - The object names are reversed (i.e. West should be East)

7. Growth Rates (Growth)

  • Purpose: Saves Predicted and Actual growth rates for commercial (\(g\)) and recruit (\(gR\)) sized scallops.

NOTE: This script requires inputs from 2. Meat Weight - Shell Height and Condition modeling (Growth) and 5. Shell Height Frequencies (Growth)

  • Overview:

    • Import outputs from previous scripts in respective areas (SPA1A, SPA1B, SPA3, SPA4and5, and SPA6) e.g. AREAgrowth2019.RData, AREA2019.SHobj.R, AREA.ActualGrowthRateObj.YYYY.R, AREAPredictedGrowthRateObj.YYYY.R

    • Imports predicted and actual shell height, MWSH.YYYY model, and meat weight shell height data from samples.

      Actual Growth Rates

    • commercial mean meat weight in year t-1 is predicted using predicted SH (SH predicted from year t-1 to year t) and actual mw/sh relationship in year t

    • recruit mean meat weight in year t-1 is predicted using predicted SH (SH predicted from year t-1 to year t) and actual mw/sh relationship in year t

    • actual commercial mean meat weight in year t is predicted and

    • actual recruit mean meat weight in year t is predicted.

      Predicted Growth Rates

    • Calculate mean weight of commercial and recruit animals:

      1. In year t (“actual”) using mean SH in year t and meat weight shell height relationship in year t

      2. In year t+1 (“pred”) using predicted mean SH in year t+1 (predicted from year t) and meat weight shell height relationship in year t

    • i.e. predicted g and gR were from year t to t+1, assuming it is unknown.

    \(g_{t-1} = \bar{w_t}/\bar{w}_{t-1}\)

  • Script Directory: To be your forked Marscal Inshore repository path (e.g. C:/Users/WILSONB/Documents/GitHub/Inshore/BoF/Growth)

  • Output(s):

    • SPA1A

      • spa1A.growthrate.YYYY.csv

      • SPA1A_GrowthRate_ComRec_Actual.png

      • SPA1A_GrowthRate_Com_ActualPredicted.png

      • SPA1A_GrowthRate_Rec_ActualPredicted.png

    • SPA1B

      • spa1B.growthrate.YYYY.csv

      • SPA1B_GrowthRate_ComRec_Actual.png

      • SPA1B_GrowthRate_Com_ActualPredicted.png

      • SPA1B_GrowthRate_Rec_ActualPredicted.png

    • SPA3

      • spa3.growthrate.YYYY.csv

      • SPA3_GrowthRate_ComRec_Actual.png

      • SPA3_GrowthRate_Com_ActualPredicted.png

      • SPA3_GrowthRate_Rec_ActualPredicted.png

    • SPA4

      • spa4.growthrate.YYYY.csv

11. Model (Model)

  • Purpose:

    • Population model - Bayesian state space model

      \(B_{t+1} = (e^{-m_t}g_t(B_t-C_t)+e^{-m_t}g_{Rt}R_t)\tau_t\)

  • Overview:

    • Model formulation for BoF: have biomass remove catch then grow up and kill off.

    • Starts by creating comparison file (SPAx_ModelData_R.xlsx). Ensure previous years data has not changed. Investigate if differences are flagged.

    • Import data from generated SPAx_ModelData_R_YYYY-MM-DD.xlsx :

      • C - Catch

      • N - population numbers

      • I - Biomass scaled to full area

      • I.cv -

      • IR - Recruit Biomass scaled to full area

      • IR.cv -

      • ratiolined - ratio of lined to unlined

      • g - Commercial growth

      • gR - recruit growth

      • clappers - clapper numbers

    • Set parameters to be returned from the winbugs model run:

      • B - Commercial Biomass (in tonnes)

      • R - Recruit Biomass (in tonnes)

      • q - Catchability

      • K - Scaling parameter

      • P - Biomass scaled by K

      • sigma

      • S - dissolution factor (factors into the clapper model)

      • m - mortality

      • kappa.tau - observation error for clappers?

      • r - recruit biomass scaled by K

      • Fmort - instant mortality

      • mu - exploitation rate

      • Irep - Commercial Biomass not scaled by q

      • IRrep - Recruit Biomass not scaled by q

      • Presid, sPresid, Iresid, IRresid, sIresid, sIRresid - residuals

    • Model is run in Winbugs and diagnostics are run (i.e. checks for model convergence)

    • Plots of time series of survey biomass estimates are made

    • Plots biomass time series (EN/FR), box plot contains 80% of the data when pred.lim = 0.2 (i.e. 80% of the data is located between the whiskers)

    • Plot of the posteriors

    • Plots of residuals

    • Plot of the predicted prediction-evaluation

    • Creates decision table and saves out model summary.

  • Script Directory: To be your forked Marscal Inshore repository path (e.g. C:/Users/WILSONB/Documents/GitHub/Inshore/BoF/Model)

  • Output(s):

    • SPAx_ModelData_R.xlsx

    • SPAx_Model_YYYY.RData

    • spaXModelOutput.csv

    • Survey_est_figure_AREA.png

    • Model_biomass_figure_AREA.png

    • plot.Presids_AREA.png, plot.sPresid_AREA.png, plot.Iresid_AREA.png. plot.IRresid_Area.png

    • Prediction_evaluation_figure_predicted_AREA.png

    • Prediction_evaluation_figure_actual_AREA.png

    • decisiontableYYYY_AREA.csv

    • SPA6_Model_YYYY.RData

    • Model_results_and_diagnostics_YYYY_AREA.RData

  • Output Directory(s):

    • Y:/Inshore/BoF/Model/AREA
